[2] Vaccine purchase

Date: Sun, 8 Apr 2012
Source: Almasryalyoum [Mach. transl., edited]
http://www.almasryalyoum.com/node/758866

Abu Naga: "11 million pounds in support of urgent purchase of 2 million doses FMD vaccine"
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Fayza Abul Naga, Minister of Planning and International Cooperation, has announced the allocation of EGP 11 million [USD 1 822 700] in support of urgent purchase, by the General Organisation for Veterinary Services, of 2 million doses of vaccine against Foot and mouth disease [FMD] strain Sat2.

Abul-Naga said in a news release Sunday [8 Apr 2012], that the Ministry of International Cooperation is currently studying ways to provide an additional amount to finance the purchase of vehicles equipped to work on the rapid diagnosis of disease epidemiology, a complement to the urgent efforts taken by the Egyptian government to face this disease.

She stressed that the Egyptian government is seeking to combat FMD in the various provinces of Egypt; the Ministry of Agriculture and Land Reclamation, Egypt is making efforts to curb the spread of the disease and contain it.

[Byline: Sana Abdul Wahab]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[The above report includes a picture of a 300 ml vial marked "FMD-VACSAT2". According to some Egyptian newspapers, vaccination has already started last week in several governorates (item 4, further).

See also he following (older) item 3. -Mod. AS].

