[3] Vaccine production

Date: Fri, 29 Mar 2012
Source: Egypt Independent, Translated from Al-Masry Al-Youm [edited]
http://www.almasryalyoum.com/node/740956

Egypt produces first foot-and-mouth vaccine
-------------------------------------------
The Holding Company for Biological Products & Vaccines (VACSERA), which is affiliated with the Health Ministry, together with Nivac Pharmaceuticals, has produced a new vaccine to immunize animals from the SAT2 strain of foot-and-mouth disease FMD] on Thursday [28 Mar 2012].

Dr. Osama Selim, head of the General Authority for Veterinary Services, said 1 million doses would be ready on Tuesday [3 Apr 2012] to be distributed among small farmers for free.

"The vaccine will be tested on Monday [2 Mar 2012]," he said, explaining that it would be given to the healthy animals to limit the spread of the disease.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[It will be interesting to note which FMDV SAT2 virus strain has been used for the manufacture of the above "new vaccine". See following item 4 on the commenced vaccination.

Details on the vaccine testing applied, in particular addressing the safety of the vaccine, will be appreciated. -Mod. AS].


