[5] Vaccination fraud

Date: Fri, 6 Apr 2012
Source: Almasryalyoum.com [Mach. transl., summarised, edited].
http://www.almasryalyoum.com/node/755356

Aswan gang exploiting "mouth" of the monument and injected cattle sera "garlic and lemon"
-----------------------------------------------------
Following a police investigation in Edfu, in the governorate of Aswan, 4 people were arrested on Fri, 6 Apr 2012, accused of fraud. They pretended to be veterinary doctors assigned by UN agency UNESCO to control FMD by vaccination. The fake vaccine they applied, charging farmers and livestock owners EGP 20 per head, was composed of garlic and garlic and lemon juice. Their car carried a poster saying "the national campaign to combat foot and mouth disease in collaboration with UNESCO". The 4, (20, 24, 25 and 33 y old) came from Sohag and Luxor.

The prosecution has taken over the investigation.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[Egypt's major FMDV SAT2 epizootic has probably approching its peak; past experience in the region has shown peaks in April-May.

The 2 main questions at present are:
- would this widely disseminated virus become endemic in Egypt?
- is the virus going to continue its spread to other counties in the region?

As shown in item 4 above, the issue has obtained serious economic dimensions in Egypt. An expression of the potential political implications is included in the following comment by Omar El Sabh, published on 5 Apr 2012 in The Daily News Egypt:

"The FJP’s [Freedom and Justice Party] threats to hold a no confidence vote over the Ganzoury government run in tandem to what the Brotherhood's leadership fears day by day, the reduction of its popularity in the street. The gas and bread crises, continued depletion of foreign reserves with no compensatory policies, the spread of the Foot and Mouth Disease in the countryside, and the continuous state of lack of security and other governmental fiascos are but a few issues that could abate the Brotherhood’s popularity". http://www.thedailynewsegypt.com/letters/mr-successful-and-scaf-dp5.html.

This is reminiscent of other major FMD outbreaks in recent years (e.g., UK, Japan, S. Korea). During the 2001 UK epizootic, the intervention of PM Tony Blair was sought and the elections had to be postponed. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1zkM.]
